review_blob:
Smells like a red wine. The blueberry is noticeable and cheese (similar to wine). It tastes even. The sour isn't overpowering because it is the perfect combo of the sweet and sour taste in a blueberry. Then the wood flavor comes out at the end of the drink. It paired well with havarti cheese but I not with the cracker

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Smell: coffee, no alcohol really, chocolate is very subtle

Taste: I get the sweet first (chocolate) and it ends with some bitter coffee flavor like espresso beans roasted with chocolate. The roast is not abundant.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
